<task id="050" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4">
  <metadata>
    <title>A-4: Raise chat attachment cap (client + server) to 25 MB and publish CHAT-ATTACHMENT-POLICY.md</title>
    <phase>Phase 5 — Substantive code changes</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>6</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>none</dependencies>
    <blocks>none</blocks>
    <tags>bff-api, frontend, react, fluent-ui, e2e-test, deploy, documentation</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Tags include 'bff-api' + 'frontend' + 'react'; modifies both .cs and .ts code; 6+ steps; touches user-facing chat surface AND BFF endpoint. Per Step 3.5.5 decision tree, FULL rigor is mandatory. CLAUDE.md §10 Placement Justification REQUIRED.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>F</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Raise the chat attachment cap end-to-end from the current values to 25 MB. (1) Client-side: update
    `MAX_FILE_BYTES` in `useChatFileAttachment.ts` (currently 10 MB) to 25 MB; update tests and user-facing
    error string. (2) Server-side: update `MaxAttachmentSizeBytes` (or equivalent constant) in
    `ChatEndpoints.cs`; review `MaxAttachmentTextCharsPerFile` (currently 2.5M) and `MaxAttachmentTextCharsTotal`
    (currently 5M) and scale proportionally if warranted; update tests. (3) Publish
    `docs/standards/CHAT-ATTACHMENT-POLICY.md` covering size cap rationale, MIME allow-list, total-text cap,
    PDF page cap, upgrade path. (4) Boundary tests at 1 MB / 10 MB / 24 MB / 26 MB. (5) Verify CLAUDE.md §10
    Placement Justification in PR notes; verify publish-size ≤60 MB compressed.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Full-stack developer with .NET 8 Minimal API + React 19 / Fluent UI v9 expertise. Familiar with BFF
    §10 hygiene rules and ADR-013 AI-architecture placement criteria. Bias toward minimal blast radius:
    raise the cap, don't redesign the attachment pipeline.
  </role>

  <goal>
    (a) `MAX_FILE_BYTES` in `useChatFileAttachment.ts` raised to `25 * 1024 * 1024` with the user-facing
    error string updated to "exceeds 25 MB"; (b) server-side `MaxAttachmentSizeBytes` and char-cap constants
    in `ChatEndpoints.cs` aligned with 25 MB cap and proportional text-char scaling decision documented;
    (c) tests at boundary sizes (1/10/24/26 MB) pass; (d) `docs/standards/CHAT-ATTACHMENT-POLICY.md` published
    covering size cap, MIME allow-list, total-text cap, PDF page cap, upgrade path; (e) CLAUDE.md §10
    Placement Justification entry in PR description; (f) `dotnet publish` ≤60 MB compressed verified.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per spec FR-04 (A-4): operator decision OC-R4-01 (2026-05-25) shifted A-4 from doc-only to code +
      policy doc + boundary tests. Original spec assumed client cap was 5 MB; verified at task start: the
      current client cap is `MAX_FILE_BYTES = 10 * 1024 * 1024` (10 MB) per `useChatFileAttachment.ts:139`.
      Other surfaces already operate at 25 MB (DocumentUploadWizard:73, OfficeService.cs:1451) — 25 MB is
      an established Spaarke standard, not a stretch. The R3 attachment feature path remains BFF in-process
      per refined ADR-013 (2026-05-20) and the F-1 retroactive memo (task 002). NFR-08 bundle-size budget:
      this is a constant change + a policy doc; bundle impact should be near-zero (text cap, not file
      binary impact). NFR-01 publish-size: must verify ≤60 MB compressed after server change. CLAUDE.md
      §10 Placement Justification: REQUIRED since this modifies a BFF endpoint.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/SprkChat/hooks/useChatFileAttachment.ts</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/SprkChat/__tests__/useChatFileAttachment.test.ts</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Ai/ChatEndpoints.cs</file>
      <file>tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Api/Ai/ChatEndpointsAttachmentsTests.cs</file>
      <file>docs/standards/CHAT-ATTACHMENT-POLICY.md</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-001">Minimal API only — no controllers. Modify the existing endpoint handler in `ChatEndpoints.cs`; do not introduce new routing patterns.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">DI minimalism — do NOT create a new feature module or service. The attachment validation lives in the existing chat endpoint pipeline; constants update only.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">AI features extend the BFF in-process (refined 2026-05-20). Attachment text extraction stays client-side; payload validation stays BFF in-process. No new AI service. CRUD code MUST NOT directly inject `IOpenAiClient` / `IPlaybookService` — N/A here since this task does not add new injections.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-028">Function-based auth — chat endpoint already uses `RequireAuthorization()` + `AddAiAuthorizationFilter()`. Do NOT modify auth posture. Do NOT introduce token snapshots in any code touched.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">BFF publish hygiene — verify `dotnet publish` ≤60 MB compressed after change. No new NuGet packages.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">CLAUDE.md §10 Placement Justification REQUIRED in PR description citing `.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md` decision criteria. Memo template: forward example for §10 (B-4 and B-5 will produce companions).</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Bundle-size impact: NFR-08 SpaarkeAi gzip ≤ +50 KB vs R3 918 KB baseline. This change is a constant + policy doc; expected impact ≈ 0. Measure before/after.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">CVE check (NFR-09): no new NuGet packages introduced; `dotnet list package --vulnerable --include-transitive` must return 0 new HIGH-severity findings.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Server-side total-text cap (`MaxAttachmentTextCharsTotal = 5_000_000`) MUST be reviewed; if not raised, document the rationale in the policy doc (text density independent of binary file size).</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Single-LLM-call invariant (R2 D-01 lesson): 25 MB attachments still flow through ONE chat message + ONE LLM call. Do NOT introduce a separate pre-extraction call.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/constraints/api.md</file>
