  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Rigor declaration">Output the mandatory rigor declaration: 🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: FULL — bff-api + frontend tags, modifies .cs/.ts code, 6+ steps, §10 BFF hygiene applies.</step>
    <step order="1" name="Confirm current state">Re-read `useChatFileAttachment.ts:136-140` and `ChatEndpoints.cs:1968-2055` to lock in the current cap values (MAX_FILE_BYTES, MaxAttachmentSizeBytes, MaxAttachmentTextCharsPerFile, MaxAttachmentTextCharsTotal). Locate the exact server-side `MaxAttachmentSizeBytes` constant (search `ChatEndpoints.cs` if not at the cited lines).</step>
    <step order="2" name="§10 Placement Justification">Draft the Placement Justification entry per `.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md` decision criteria: (a) Is this AI-coupled? (yes — chat is the AI surface); (b) Is the in-process answer correct? (yes — text extraction stays client-side, validation stays BFF in-process per ADR-013); (c) Publish-size impact? (constants only); (d) CVE impact? (no new packages). Stash in PR notes or `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4/notes/`.</step>
    <step order="3" name="Update client-side cap">Edit `useChatFileAttachment.ts` line 139: `MAX_FILE_BYTES = 25 * 1024 * 1024`. Update the user-facing error message string (line ~375) to reflect 25 MB. Search for any other 10 MB / 5 MB references in the same file and adjust if found.</step>
    <step order="4" name="Update client tests">Edit `useChatFileAttachment.test.ts`: replace 10 MB / 5 MB assertions with 25 MB. Add boundary cases at 1 MB / 10 MB / 24 MB / 26 MB if not already present.</step>
    <step order="5" name="Update server-side cap">Locate and update the server-side equivalent in `ChatEndpoints.cs`. Decide whether to scale `MaxAttachmentTextCharsPerFile` / `MaxAttachmentTextCharsTotal`: a 25 MB binary cap does NOT imply a higher text cap (a 25 MB PDF may still extract to &lt;1M chars). Document the decision in the policy doc. If scaled, also update related test fixtures.</step>
    <step order="6" name="Update server tests">Edit `ChatEndpointsAttachmentsTests.cs`: add 1/10/24/26 MB boundary cases; verify clear user-facing error at 26 MB rejection (matches FR-04 acceptance criterion).</step>
    <step order="7" name="Write CHAT-ATTACHMENT-POLICY.md">Create `docs/standards/CHAT-ATTACHMENT-POLICY.md` covering: size cap rationale (25 MB matches DocumentUploadWizard + OfficeService standards); MIME allow-list (4 types: PDF, DOCX, plain text, Markdown); total-text cap policy + rationale; PDF max-page cap (200); upgrade path (how to raise in the future); cross-link to ADR-013 + the §10 Placement Justification model.</step>
    <step order="8" name="Build verification (client)">Run `npm run build` in `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components`. Verify 0 errors. Run `npm test` for `useChatFileAttachment.test.ts`. Capture before/after bundle size if directly measurable.</step>
    <step order="9" name="Build verification (server)">Run `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` — verify 0 errors / 0 new warnings. Run `dotnet test --filter "FullyQualifiedName~ChatEndpoints"` — verify all pass.</step>
    <step order="9.5" name="Quality gates">Invoke `code-review` skill and `adr-check` skill against changes. Quality gates MANDATORY (FULL rigor). Capture findings; fix any HIGH-severity before proceeding. Verify §10 BFF hygiene enforcement passes (skills updated 2026-05-21 per recent commit).</step>
    <step order="10" name="Publish-size check (NFR-01)">Run `dotnet publish -c Release src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` and verify compressed publish size ≤60 MB. Record actual size + delta vs baseline in PR notes. Per CLAUDE.md §10 — binding workflow rule.</step>
    <step order="11" name="CVE check (NFR-09)">Run `dotnet list package --vulnerable --include-transitive` — verify 0 new HIGH-severity findings. (No new packages expected.)</step>
    <step order="12" name="UI test execution">Invoke `ui-test` skill against SpaarkeAi chat surface for the three UI tests defined in &lt;ui-tests&gt; below.</step>
    <step order="13" name="Deploy">Deploy BFF via `bff-deploy` skill (Azure App Service); deploy SpaarkeAi via `code-page-deploy` skill if SprkChat is in the SpaarkeAi bundle. Verify deployment ping/health checks pass.</step>
    <step order="14" name="Update TASK-INDEX">Edit `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4/tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: flip task 050 status 🔲 → ✅. Update current-task.md per CLAUDE.md §7.</step>
    <step order="15" name="Document deviations">If any deviation (e.g., text-char caps NOT scaled proportionally with a documented rationale, or boundary edge case discovered), record in `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4/notes/` for R4 lessons-learned.</step>
  </steps>

