  <ui-tests>
    <test name="Upload 25 MB attachment succeeds">
      <url>https://{org}.crm.dynamics.com/main.aspx?appid={app-id}&amp;pagetype=custom&amp;name=sprk_spaarkeai</url>
      <steps>
        <step>Open SpaarkeAi page → Assistant pane → start a chat</step>
        <step>Click the `+` attach button</step>
        <step>Select a ~25 MB PDF file (just under the cap)</step>
        <step>Wait for client-side text extraction to complete</step>
        <step>Verify the attachment chip appears with status "ready"</step>
        <step>Send the chat message</step>
        <step>Verify the BFF accepts the request (no 4xx rejection)</step>
        <step>Verify the LLM response references the attachment content</step>
      </steps>
      <expected>Attachment uploads, extracts, and is included in the chat send; LLM responds referencing attachment content.</expected>
    </test>

    <test name="Upload 26 MB attachment rejected with clear error">
      <url>https://{org}.crm.dynamics.com/main.aspx?appid={app-id}&amp;pagetype=custom&amp;name=sprk_spaarkeai</url>
      <steps>
        <step>Open SpaarkeAi page → Assistant pane → start a chat</step>
        <step>Click the `+` attach button</step>
        <step>Select a ~26 MB file (just over the cap)</step>
        <step>Verify the rejection error appears in the chat surface</step>
        <step>Verify the error message says "exceeds 25 MB" (or near-identical wording)</step>
        <step>Verify the chip does NOT enter "ready" state — only an error chip is shown</step>
        <step>Verify console has no uncaught JS errors</step>
      </steps>
      <expected>Client rejects with clear user-facing "exceeds 25 MB" error; no network call to BFF; no console errors.</expected>
    </test>

    <test name="Multi-file at total 25 MB succeeds">
      <url>https://{org}.crm.dynamics.com/main.aspx?appid={app-id}&amp;pagetype=custom&amp;name=sprk_spaarkeai</url>
      <steps>
        <step>Open SpaarkeAi page → Assistant pane → start a chat</step>
        <step>Attach 3 files totaling ~25 MB (e.g., 10 MB + 10 MB + 5 MB)</step>
        <step>Verify all 3 chips reach "ready" status</step>
        <step>Send the chat message</step>
        <step>Verify BFF accepts; the single LLM call includes all 3 attachments (R2 D-01 single-LLM-call invariant)</step>
      </steps>
      <expected>Multiple files within per-file caps work; payload sent as a single chat message + single LLM call.</expected>
    </test>
  </ui-tests>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">Given a 24 MB attachment, When the user attaches it in chat, Then the chip reaches "ready" status and the message sends successfully.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given a 25 MB attachment, When the user attaches it in chat, Then it is accepted at the boundary (FR-04 acceptance).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given a 26 MB attachment, When the user attaches it, Then it is rejected with a clear user-facing error referencing the 25 MB limit (FR-04 acceptance).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given the BFF endpoint, When a request exceeds the server-side `MaxAttachmentSizeBytes`, Then the BFF returns a 4xx with a clear error body.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given `docs/standards/CHAT-ATTACHMENT-POLICY.md` exists, When read, Then it covers size cap rationale, MIME allow-list, total-text cap, PDF max-page cap, and upgrade path.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given the §10 Placement Justification rule, When the PR is opened, Then PR notes contain a Placement Justification entry citing `.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md` decision criteria.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given the NFR-01 publish-size rule, When `dotnet publish -c Release` is run, Then the compressed publish size is ≤60 MB and the delta vs baseline is recorded in PR notes.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given NFR-09 CVE policy, When `dotnet list package --vulnerable --include-transitive` is run, Then 0 new HIGH-severity findings are reported.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given the single-LLM-call invariant (R2 D-01), When 25 MB of attachments are sent, Then exactly ONE chat message + ONE LLM call is made (no separate pre-extraction round-trip).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">All unit + integration tests pass (`dotnet test` for ChatEndpoints tests; `npm test` for useChatFileAttachment tests).</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    Spec said "raise from 5 MB → 25 MB" — verified at task start that current client cap is 10 MB (not 5 MB).
    The end-state target (25 MB) is unchanged; just the delta size differs. The 5 MB figure in spec is
    historical. Update the §10 Placement Justification entry to cite the actual delta (10 → 25 MB).
    Server-side `MaxAttachmentTextCharsPerFile` (2.5M) and `MaxAttachmentTextCharsTotal` (5M) are independent
    of the binary cap — a 25 MB PDF often extracts to ≤1M chars. Reviewing them is required per spec; raising
    them is OPTIONAL with a documented rationale (the policy doc is the right place for that rationale).
  </notes>

